```
1. Update your ESLint configuration file (e.g., `.eslintrc.json` or `.eslintrc.js`) to include the plugin and enable the rule:
```json
{
  "plugins": ["no-profanity"],
  "rules": {
    "no-profanity/no-profanity": "error"
  }
}
```
